<br>
I was in shock. :) <br>
<br>
The problem is, I wasn't really expecting to get one for a VERY long time! I'm a half elf druid in a smallish guild, so I don't exactly have a lot of great equipment. Before the shield, I held the Testament to get my wis up to a whopping 191. (Base wisdom of 90, go me.) So now it's down to 181. <br>
<br>
So I was looking on a little advice! Is the AC better with my wisdom so low? I guess I can trade out depending on the situation, but I'm trying to decide if the mana loss is worth holding the shield all the time. (I'm of course going to look for better wisdom items, but nothing is easy to get.)<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading! <p><center><img src="http://37thchamber.com/Illumin/images/Profile/mist_sig.jpg"><br>
