</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uactinide.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Actinide</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/29/01 2:40:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3249.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.winco.net/~polage/Kibartik.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sarnak Battle Shield (lehp!)</span><hr size=1> don't worry about it, if you are going to solo, then switch to the testament, otherwise use the shield, 100 mana (10 wis points) isn't going to make a big difference when you are grouped.  181 wis is still a lot of mana, and the extra AC never hurts. <p>
<img src="http://web.winco.net/~polage/act_denksig.gif">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukenuon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenuon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/29/01 10:48:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3249.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sarnak Battle Shield (lehp!)</span><hr size=1> Go the shield. Not only does it have great ac and resists its still the best looking shield out there. :) Dropping your wis to 181 as Actinide pointed out, still gives you plenty of mana. If you need to quad kite, do alot of prefight buffing, just swap out. <br>
